Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State on Friday appointed Mr. Tayo Ayinde as his Chief of Staff and Mr. Gboyega Soyannwo as deputy chief of staff. This was contained in a statement by Sanwo-Oluâ€™s Deputy Chief Press Secretary, Mr. Gboyega Akosile. Ayinde, an alumnus of Havard Business School, Boston, USA and University of Cambridge, United Kingdom was the Director General of the Babajide Sanwo-Olu Independent Campaign Group between 2018 and 2019. He is a former security and intelligence personnel. He had previously served as chief security detail to the former Governor of Lagos State, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu from 1999 to 2007. Soyannwo, a seasoned banker has worked in various management capacity between 2005 to 2009 heading various strategic units. until his present appointment, Soyannwo was Managing Consultant at Cranbrook Financial Consulting Services. The appointments take immediate effect, according to Akosile.